      "content": "Substantive due process is a constitutional doctrine that allows courts to protect fundamental liberties not explicitly listed in the text, such as the right to privacy and reproductive freedom. This concept has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by invalidating laws that infringe upon personal autonomy, like those restricting contraception or abortion. By interpreting the Fourteenth Amendment broadly, the judiciary has ensured that government actions must respect deep-seated individual rights even when they aren't directly mentioned in the Constitution.",
