    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That sounds like a good start. I want to make sure I emphasize the importance of this doctrine for my students. Some critics argue that this kind of \"broad interpretation\" is just making up new rights that aren't actually in the Constitution. How should I address that in the lesson so they understand why the substantive due process approach is the more correct or legitimate way to view the law?",
